name: test-generation
description: >
  Generate comprehensive unit tests, integration tests, or end-to-end tests
  for existing code. Use when a user wants test coverage added to a function,
  module, class, or API endpoint.

version: "1.0"
author: VaultWares

instructions: |
  Test generation workflow:

  1. Identify the testing framework in use:
     Python   → pytest (preferred) or unittest
     JS/TS    → Jest or Vitest
     Go       → testing package
     Java     → JUnit 5
     If none is specified, default to the ecosystem standard above.

  2. Cover these case types for every function:
     - Happy path    — valid input, expected output
     - Edge case     — empty, zero, null, boundary values
     - Error case    — invalid input, should raise/reject
     - State change  — verify side effects (DB write, file created, etc.)

  3. Follow AAA structure:
     Arrange → set up data
     Act     → call the function
     Assert  → verify outcome

  4. Name tests descriptively:
     test_<function>_<scenario>_<expected_outcome>
     Example: test_recommend_model_complex_prompt_returns_max

  5. Mock external dependencies (network, DB, file I/O) using the
     framework's standard mock library.

  6. Output: runnable test file with all imports.
     Do not include implementation code in the test file.

  Model tier: standard for unit tests; max for integration test suites.
